Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.84,0:01:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,THE LAND ON THE FAR BANK
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.28,0:02:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the fish biting?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.74,0:02:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The fish are already in hibernation, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.32,0:02:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care if I don't catch anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.87,0:02:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,My real job is operating the ferry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.29,0:02:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys are Danes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.75,0:02:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You speak good English,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.30,0:02:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but you have a bit of an accent.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.01,0:02:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Your accent sounds just like people from my country.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.97,0:02:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How much would it cost to take us to\Nthe opposite shore?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.64,0:02:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Two silver pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.52,0:02:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't have silver, I also take alcohol.\NWell, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.35,0:02:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder how many days it would take me to bring\Nall of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.44,0:02:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I only need you to bring this letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.03,0:03:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you were customers. That's too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.16,0:03:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, who do you want me to deliver it to?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.00,0:03:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,To any one of the elders. It's urgent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.75,0:03:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell them it's from Askeladd,\Nson of Lydia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.89,0:03:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood. I'll hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.41,0:03:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Askeladd!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.62,0:03:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Askeladd! Where are you? Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.17,0:03:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ragnar. Please be quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.13,0:03:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you stop the march?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.00,0:04:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thorkell is going to catch up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.80,0:04:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not supposed to make noise\Nwhile The Ear is at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.30,0:04:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ear?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.10,0:04:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Bjorn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.18,0:04:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let that conehead breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.39,0:04:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ear! What’s the status?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.02,0:04:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They've gotten closer since yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.73,0:04:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hear soldiers and horses marching.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.53,0:04:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There's about 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.86,0:04:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They're close behind us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.20,0:04:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They're only one day away on foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.33,0:04:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.29,0:04:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, you said they were two days away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.42,0:04:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't trust my ears?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.50,0:04:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That was fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.29,0:04:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They're marching fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.21,0:04:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll catch up to us in just a few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.30,0:04:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Quiet, you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.14,0:04:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Horses. On the hill. Two of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.57,0:05:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They've got us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.95,0:05:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.28,0:05:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If we're going to meet them\Nin battle, we must take positions!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.24,0:05:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's impossible.\NWe're no match for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.54,0:05:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we don't do anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.83,0:05:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I've sent a request for reinforcements.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.88,0:05:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll keep running until they arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.80,0:05:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,-What?\N-Reinforcements?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.44,0:05:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,NOVEMBER 1013 AD WEST ENGLAND\NDOWNSTREAM EAST BANK OF SEVERN RIVER
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.81,0:05:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Reinforcements?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.44,0:05:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We're deep in enemy territory!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.48,0:05:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what Askeladd said, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.65,0:05:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He's never lied to us about something like that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.24,0:05:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.32,0:05:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But where's the closest fort?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.20,0:05:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Leicester.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.45,0:05:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously? It'll take two weeks to get there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.58,0:05:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if the reinforcements will be in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.92,0:06:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If we ask for reinforcements, we have to\Nsplit the plunder, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.13,0:06:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Askeladd said we could handle it ourselves\Nwith just the hundred of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.96,0:06:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so tired! I want to get back on a ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.43,0:06:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.35,0:06:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A ship would be nice...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.29,0:06:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Do you need something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.51,0:06:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.88,0:06:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You should give them an explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.89,0:06:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Let them worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.98,0:07:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Worrying will make them march faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.27,0:07:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.82,0:07:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's all, then go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.11,0:07:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been acting weird the last few days.\NWhat are you up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.95,0:07:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since you saw the prince's face. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.21,0:07:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been living among criminals\Nfor 40 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.68,0:07:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell what a man is like,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.64,0:07:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,whether he's a big shot or a nobody,\Nwhether he's smart
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.39,0:07:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or stupid, just by looking at his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.69,0:07:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,When I saw the prince's face, I could tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.44,0:07:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,"That's not the face of a king."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.87,0:07:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,True. He looks like a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.16,0:08:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's still a kid, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.87,0:08:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true. He's still young. His future still awaits.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.84,0:08:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What? His future still awaits?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.71,0:08:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! Wake up, guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.34,0:08:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Get ready to march! If you're slow,\NThorkell is going to catch up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.39,0:08:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.10,0:08:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.52,0:09:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.69,0:09:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yeah?\N-Were you able to sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.73,0:09:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.74,0:09:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.78,0:09:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up. Be quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.62,0:09:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I don't keep talking,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.79,0:09:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to fall asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.54,0:09:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This is bad, Askeladd. They're right behind us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.00,0:09:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.92,0:09:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to catch up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.76,0:09:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.05,0:09:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We're almost to where the reinforcements will come.\NRight there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.69,0:09:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,-Reinforcements?\N-Them? Just the two of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.99,0:10:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's just an illusion made by the fog.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.05,0:10:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so honored that the commander has come himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.68,0:10:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a long time, Askeladd.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.05,0:11:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.39,0:11:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you're saying a ship carried them across the river?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.89,0:11:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know whose ship it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.89,0:11:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.02,0:11:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The fog was as thick as goat's milk.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.57,0:11:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't a Norse ship. It didn't have a dragonhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.86,0:11:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It was kind of pudgy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.91,0:11:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It had an eye drawn on it. On the bow. Big, like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.12,0:11:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't sound like one of King Sweyn's ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.33,0:11:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, we can't follow Thorfinn anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.46,0:11:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I underestimated them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.76,0:11:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think that the people across the Severn River\Nwere their allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.89,0:11:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean the people across the river\Nswitched sides from England to Denmark?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.81,0:11:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You idiot! You don't know anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.02,0:11:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The land on the other side of this river isn't\Npart of England in the first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.07,0:12:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Wales.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.99,0:12:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Wales is a mountainous region to the west of England.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.83,0:12:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The steep mountains had few natural resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.83,0:12:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Flat land suitable for agriculture was scarce.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.04,0:12:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The land was poor compared to England.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.38,0:12:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,After the end of rule by the Roman Empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.01,0:12:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Wales was never unified under a single country.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.22,0:12:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The region was divided into many\Nsmall, rival kingdoms for hundreds of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.40,0:12:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Askeladd's request for reinforcements was answered
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.02,0:12:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,by one of those small kingdoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.57,0:12:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,EAST OF MORGANNWG KINGDOM\NWALES
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.57,0:12:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to compliment you for this, Askeladd.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.91,0:12:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thorkell must be clenching his teeth in anger\Non the other side of the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.58,0:12:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If we continue going by sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.87,0:12:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we can return to Gainsborough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.46,0:13:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No. We're going to go by land.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.59,0:13:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?\NThere's a ship right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.59,0:13:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't look at it from the perspective\Nof a large nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.43,0:13:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,For this country, even three warships\Nare a valuable asset.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.64,0:13:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to be thankful that they helped us\Nescape from Thorkell in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.15,0:13:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we can make do with only two ships!\NWe can all fit!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.07,0:13:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No. If you keep acting selfish,\NI'm going to leave you behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.95,0:13:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you telling me to walk across Wales?\NThat's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.99,0:13:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The people in this land hate us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.04,0:13:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't allow you to endanger His Highness any further!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.09,0:13:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,A hawk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.13,0:13:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so low.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.46,0:13:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Ragnar. Catch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.88,0:13:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon me, Your Highness, we're in the middle\Nof something important.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.30,0:13:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better than moving north through England\Nwith Thorkell at our heels.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.06,0:13:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, this country is an ally of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.69,0:14:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're still worried...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.40,0:14:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thorfinn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.24,0:14:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll assign him to guard Canute.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.87,0:14:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! You're the guy from back there...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.87,0:14:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make the decision for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.46,0:14:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He's small, but he's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.96,0:14:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's the same age as His Highness.\NI'm sure they'll get along.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.46,0:14:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Say your greetings, Thorfinn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.89,0:14:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you an idiot?\NWhat are you glaring at him for?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.02,0:14:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to reward me for this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.23,0:14:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, all right.\NWhen we get to Gainsborough, I'll duel you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.98,0:14:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Askeladd. Are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.28,0:14:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We just finished.\NOh, my. We're so busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.45,0:14:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the general of the Kingdom of Morgannwg,\NGratianus.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.87,0:15:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He's going to show us the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.21,0:15:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a threatening look about you,\Nbut you have a good face.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.22,0:15:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, that's one of my men.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.72,0:15:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,His Highness Prince Canute is over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.52,0:15:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,His eyes look weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.19,0:15:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he really going to be the next ruler of England?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.11,0:15:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What? You bastard! How rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.61,0:15:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one reason\Nwe're helping the Danish prince escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.66,0:15:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so that we can enter a treaty of non-aggression.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.87,0:15:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all up to you. Prince, swear
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.29,0:15:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that once you become the king of England,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.79,0:15:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll never interfere in the matters of Wales.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.06,0:16:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.64,0:16:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,His Highness says,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.35,0:16:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"If you give us three ships--"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.98,0:16:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked the prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.98,0:16:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.87,0:16:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind. I'll ask again later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.71,0:16:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll prepare a written document in the meantime.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.75,0:16:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Get ready to depart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.76,0:16:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with that arrogant snob?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.18,0:16:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He's taking advantage of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.51,0:16:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he think he's an equal to the prince?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.18,0:16:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That country bumpkin!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.28,0:16:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Marching, marching, and more marching!\NNow we're marching in the mountains!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.95,0:16:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mountains are better than Thorkell.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.87,0:16:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about something more fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.99,0:17:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Like what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.70,0:17:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Our reward from King Sweyn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.91,0:17:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We saved the prince from Thorkell.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.46,0:17:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I want a farm!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.25,0:17:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I want a cool sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.13,0:17:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No. It's all about the gold. Nothing's better than gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.76,0:17:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.89,0:17:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard the king has
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.85,0:17:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,a hundred beautiful slave women\Nfrom around the world in his bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.60,0:17:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.27,0:17:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so excited! Is there anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.36,0:17:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, priest!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.40,0:17:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been to the palace, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.82,0:17:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What does the king have in his house?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.08,0:17:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there was nothing of value in particular.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.00,0:17:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! Not even beautiful women?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.04,0:17:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he did have a lot of slave women.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.09,0:17:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Aren't you interested?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.76,0:17:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't like women?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.55,0:18:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Gold, silver, and beautiful women are all nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.26,0:18:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,compared to the thing I seek.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.48,0:18:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell us! What is it you're seeking?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.70,0:18:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Love.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.16,0:18:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,-What? Love?\N-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.91,0:18:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that? I've never heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.74,0:18:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what it is. It's like a spell\Nthat the Christians are always chanting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.92,0:18:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it some kind of food?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.42,0:18:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,How many pounds in silver?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.25,0:18:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be measured in silver,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.46,0:18:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because love is what gives value to silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.34,0:18:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Without love, gold, silver, and beautiful women\Nare all worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.51,0:18:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,"Gives value"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.97,0:18:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.27,0:18:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Silver has the value of silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.60,0:18:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make it so difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.98,0:18:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He's bluffing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.61,0:18:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Just ignore him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.07,0:19:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.32,0:19:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep talking. I want to hear more.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.21,0:19:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We're about to enter the Kingdom of Brycheiniog.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.50,0:19:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. I've talked to them already.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.63,0:19:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.09,0:19:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not doing this for you.\NIt's just that our interests are aligned.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.35,0:19:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The Welsh kingdoms have always been
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.81,0:19:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,threatened by invasions from England.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.06,0:19:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you Danes can make them stop,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.48,0:19:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be good for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.90,0:19:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure His Highness the Prince will promise you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.86,0:19:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So, is that your king, Askeladd?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.28,0:19:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He's from a good bloodline.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.45,0:19:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,As for the rest, I have high hopes for him\Nsince he's young.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.63,0:19:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The more you fall for a man,\Nthe less things go how you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.59,0:20:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe someone like him is just what we need.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.18,0:20:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We're the descendants of Britannia.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.10,0:20:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not going to follow the king of the Danes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.48,0:20:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Gratianus.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.61,0:20:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you still believe in the legend?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.32,0:20:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The legend that Artorius will return\Nfrom Avalon to the west
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.11,0:20:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and restore the Britannia of old.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.38,0:20:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Askeladd!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.30,0:20:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.67,0:20:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what The Ear says.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.55,0:20:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming, prince of the Danes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.43,0:20:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They're messengers from Brycheiniog.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.31,0:20:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.90,0:21:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! Gratianus.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.70,0:21:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.32,0:21:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.95,0:21:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,One of my men has good hearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.03,0:21:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.00,0:21:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Thorfinn?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.64,0:22:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Get up! Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.86,0:22:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
